[MK] cases #13CF306 and #14CF34 called at 10:18am. 
Defendant Kimberly L Rostollan in court, in custody, with Attorney Whitney Hagemann.  ADA Monica Hall appears for the State of Wisconsin.
Two corrections are made to the Revocation Report related to the type of pending charge, and as to prison programming eligibility.  
Sentencing arguments given by counsel.
Ms. Rostollan makes a statement.

On Case #13CF306, Count #1:  The Court sentences Ms. Rostollan to an Initial Term of Confinement in Prison of 5 years, and the maximum time to serve on Extended Supervision of 5 years.  This sentence is consecutive to any previously imposed sentence 
The Court gives 363 days credit for time already served.

On Case #14CF34, Count #2:  The Court sentences Ms. Rostollan to an Initial Term of Confinement in Prison of 3  years, and the maximum time to serve on Extended Supervision of 3 years.  This sentence is concurrent to Case #13CF306.  
The Court gives 363 days credit for time already served.

As to both cases:   
The Court finds that Ms. Rostollan is eligible for the Earned Release Program. Ms. Rostallan may participate in the Earned Release Program when and if approved by the Department of Corrections, however Ms. Rostollan will not be released from prison prior to May 12th, 2019.
The Court finds that Ms. Rostollan is eligible for the Substance Abuse Program.

The Court orders as conditions of Extended Supervision:
--to undergo alcohol and other drug abuse counseling and treament as required by the Agent 
--not to have any contact with any known drug offenders except for treatment purposes as approved by the Agent
--to maintain absolute sobriety 
--no possession or consumption of illegal drugs
--no possession or consumption of alcohol
--no possess of drug paraphernalia
--no presence in bars, taverns, liquor stores 
--to pay any oustanding financial obligations including previously ordered court costs, fees, assessments, and surcharges
